<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-06-25T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-06-25T20:00:00-05:00" n="554" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d554">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">819.51/316: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Price</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-06-25T20:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">June 25,
                                        1921—8 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received June 27—9:20
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>117. Contract referred to in 115<note n="12" xml:id="d554fn12">Not
                                printed.</note> and 116 returned to International Banking
                            Corporation today approved by the President but with a letter from
                            Secretary of the Treasury canceling from July 1st former order requiring
                            countersignature Fiscal Agent and directing that all funds left with
                            said bank after said date must be considered subject to checking by the
                            sole signature of Secretary of the Treasury.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Price</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>